<section class="py-16 md:py-24 bg-slate-50">
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-7xl px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
    <article class="max-w-2xl mx-auto">
      <h2 class="font-display text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-bold text-slate-900 text-center mb-12">
        The space between your life and your limits.
      </h2>

      <blockquote class="border-l-4 border-storehouse-500 pl-6 py-4 bg-white rounded-r-lg shadow-sm">
        <p class="text-xl font-display text-slate-700 italic">
          "Margin is the space between our load and our limits."
        </p>
        <cite class="block mt-3 text-sm text-slate-500 not-italic">
          - Richard Swenson
        </cite>
      </blockquote>

      <div class="mt-10 space-y-6 text-lg text-slate-600 leading-relaxed">
        <p>
          Applied to finances, margin is the gap between what you earn and what you spend. It's the cushion that absorbs life's surprises. It's the reserve that lets you breathe.
        </p>

        <p>
          Margin isn't about having less. It's about having space.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="mt-12 grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
        <div class="p-6 bg-white rounded-xl border border-slate-200">
          <h3 class="font-display text-lg font-semibold text-slate-400">
            Living at the edge
          </h3>
          <p class="mt-3 text-slate-600">
            Every dollar accounted for. Every expense justified. Any surprise becomes a crisis. Generosity feels impossible.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-6 bg-storehouse-50 rounded-xl border border-storehouse-200">
          <h3 class="font-display text-lg font-semibold text-storehouse-700">
            Living with margin
          </h3>
          <p class="mt-3 text-slate-600">
            Room to respond. Space to give. Capacity for the unexpected. Peace instead of panic.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </article>
  </div>
</section>
